body:
You can just do:

``` js
require("pug").render(pugString, {
  filters:  {
    content: function (block) {
      return 'some string';
    }
  }
})
```

I think we should maybe support specifying filters using the old way as well as this new way.

issue.body:
I'd like to implement simple :striptags filter. Something as simple as

``` javascript
function striptags(html)
{
   var tmp = document.createElement("DIV");
   tmp.innerHTML = html;
   return tmp.textContent||tmp.innerText;
}
```

How can I teach Jade to recognize it ?

